053/**
054 * Simplex noise functions, in 2D, 3D, 4D, 5D, and 6D, with 4D and 6D as options for generating seamlessly-tiling noise
055 * using {@link Noise#seamless2D(double[][], long, int, Noise.Noise4D)} and/or
056 * {@link Noise#seamless3D(double[][][], long, int, Noise.Noise6D)}. All functions can take a long seed that should
057 * significantly change the pattern of noise produced. Incorporates code from Joise; the full library is available at
058 * https://github.com/SudoPlayGames/Joise , and this class adds rather significant optimization in a few methods,
059 * especially 6D noise. Joise is derived from the Accidental Noise Library, available in C++ at
060 * http://accidentalnoise.sourceforge.net/index.html . Both Joise and ANL have many features that SquidLib has not (yet)
061 * incorporated, but now that SquidLib has seamless noise, that's a nice feature that would have needed Joise before.
062 * This also supplies 5D noise, which doesn't have an immediate application like taking 6D noise and making 3D seamless
063 * noise, but still has plenty of uses. <a href="http://yellowstonegames.github.io/SquidLib/AnimatedChangingGlobe.gif">This
064 * world GIF</a> was made using 5D noise, for instance, using a cycle through the 4th and 5th dimensions to alter the
065 * globe in a way that loops. You'd probably find yourself mostly using 2D through 4D, though, with 4D useful for 3D
066 * shapes that change linearly over time.
067 */
068public class SeededNoise implements Noise.Noise2D, Noise.Noise3D, Noise.Noise4D, Noise.Noise5D, Noise.Noise6D {

081    protected static double gradCoord2D(long seed, int x, int y, double xd, double yd) {
082        final double[] g = grad2d[HastyPointHash.hash256(x, y, seed)];
083        return xd * g[0] + yd * g[1];
084    }
085    /**
086     * Computes the hash for a 3D int point and its dot product with a 3D double point as one step.
087     * @param seed
088     * @param x
089     * @param y
090     * @param z
091     * @param xd
092     * @param yd
093     * @param zd
094     * @return a double between -1.2571 and 1.2571, exclusive
095     */
096    protected static double gradCoord3D(long seed, int x, int y, int z, double xd, double yd, double zd) {
097        final int hash = HastyPointHash.hash32(x, y, z, seed) * 3;
098        return xd * grad3d[hash] + yd * grad3d[hash + 1] + zd * grad3d[hash + 2];
099    }
100    protected static double gradCoord5D(long seed, int x, int y, int z, int w, int u, double xd, double yd, double zd, double wd, double ud) {
101        final int hash = HastyPointHash.hash256(x, y, z, w, u, seed) * 5;
102        return xd * grad5d[hash] + yd * grad5d[hash + 1] + zd * grad5d[hash + 2] + wd * grad5d[hash + 3] + ud * grad5d[hash + 4];
103    }

158    protected static final double F2 = 0.36602540378443864676372317075294,
159            G2 = 0.21132486540518711774542560974902,
160            H2 = G2 * 2.0,
161            F3 = 1.0 / 3.0,
162            G3 = 1.0 / 6.0,
163            F4 = (Math.sqrt(5.0) - 1.0) * 0.25,
164            G4 = (5.0 - Math.sqrt(5.0)) * 0.05,
165            LIMIT4 = 0.62,
166            F5 = (Math.sqrt(6.0) - 1.0) / 5.0,
167            G5 = (6.0 - Math.sqrt(6.0)) / 30.0,
168            LIMIT5 = 0.7,
169            F6 = (Math.sqrt(7.0) - 1.0) / 6.0,
170            G6 = F6 / (1.0 + 6.0 * F6),
171            LIMIT6 = 0.8375;

173    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final long seed) {
174        double t = (x + y) * F2;
175        int i = fastFloor(x + t);
176        int j = fastFloor(y + t);
177
178        t = (i + j) * G2;
179        double X0 = i - t;
180        double Y0 = j - t;
181
182        double x0 = x - X0;
183        double y0 = y - Y0;
184
185        int i1, j1;
186        if (x0 > y0) {
187            i1 = 1;
188            j1 = 0;
189        } else {
190            i1 = 0;
191            j1 = 1;
192        }
193
194        double x1 = x0 - i1 + G2;
195        double y1 = y0 - j1 + G2;
196        double x2 = x0 - 1 + H2;
197        double y2 = y0 - 1 + H2;
198
199        double n = 0.0;
200
201        t = 0.5 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0;
202        if (t >= 0) {
203            t *= t;
204            n += t * t * gradCoord2D(seed, i, j, x0, y0);
205        }
206
207        t = 0.5 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1;
208        if (t > 0) {
209            t *= t;
210            n += t * t * gradCoord2D(seed, i + i1, j + j1, x1, y1);
211        }
212
213        t = 0.5 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2;
214        if (t > 0)  {
215            t *= t;
216            n += t * t * gradCoord2D(seed, i + 1, j + 1, x2, y2);
217        }
218        return n * 99.20689070704672; // this is 99.83685446303647 / 1.00635 ; the first number was found by kdotjpg
219    }

221    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final long seed) {
222        double n = 0.0;
223        final double s = (x + y + z) * F3;
224        final int i = fastFloor(x + s),
225                j = fastFloor(y + s),
226                k = fastFloor(z + s);
227
228        final double t = (i + j + k) * G3;
229        final double X0 = i - t, Y0 = j - t, Z0 = k - t,
230                x0 = x - X0, y0 = y - Y0, z0 = z - Z0;
231
232        int i1, j1, k1;
233        int i2, j2, k2;
234
235        if (x0 >= y0) {
236            if (y0 >= z0) {
237                i1 = 1;
238                j1 = 0;
239                k1 = 0;
240                i2 = 1;
241                j2 = 1;
242                k2 = 0;
243            } else if (x0 >= z0) {
244                i1 = 1;
245                j1 = 0;
246                k1 = 0;
247                i2 = 1;
248                j2 = 0;
249                k2 = 1;
250            } else {
251                i1 = 0;
252                j1 = 0;
253                k1 = 1;
254                i2 = 1;
255                j2 = 0;
256                k2 = 1;
257            }
258        } else {
259            if (y0 < z0) {
260                i1 = 0;
261                j1 = 0;
262                k1 = 1;
263                i2 = 0;
264                j2 = 1;
265                k2 = 1;
266            } else if (x0 < z0) {
267                i1 = 0;
268                j1 = 1;
269                k1 = 0;
270                i2 = 0;
271                j2 = 1;
272                k2 = 1;
273            } else {
274                i1 = 0;
275                j1 = 1;
276                k1 = 0;
277                i2 = 1;
278                j2 = 1;
279                k2 = 0;
280            }
281        }
282
283        double x1 = x0 - i1 + G3; // Offsets for second corner in (x,y,z) coords
284        double y1 = y0 - j1 + G3;
285        double z1 = z0 - k1 + G3;
286        double x2 = x0 - i2 + F3; // Offsets for third corner in (x,y,z) coords
287        double y2 = y0 - j2 + F3;
288        double z2 = z0 - k2 + F3;
289        double x3 = x0 - 0.5; // Offsets for last corner in (x,y,z) coords
290        double y3 = y0 - 0.5;
291        double z3 = z0 - 0.5;
292
293        // Calculate the contribution from the four corners
294        double t0 = 0.6 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0 - z0 * z0;
295        if (t0 > 0) {
296            t0 *= t0;
297            n += t0 * t0 * gradCoord3D(seed, i, j, k, x0, y0, z0);
298        }
299        double t1 = 0.6 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1 - z1 * z1;
300        if (t1 > 0) {
301            t1 *= t1;
302            n += t1 * t1 * gradCoord3D(seed, i + i1, j + j1, k + k1, x1, y1, z1);
303        }
304        double t2 = 0.6 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2 - z2 * z2;
305        if (t2 > 0) {
306            t2 *= t2;
307            n += t2 * t2 * gradCoord3D(seed, i + i2, j + j2, k + k2, x2, y2, z2);
308        }
309        double t3 = 0.6 - x3 * x3 - y3 * y3 - z3 * z3;
310        if (t3 > 0) {
311            t3 *= t3;
312            n += t3 * t3 * gradCoord3D(seed, i + 1, j + 1, k + 1, x3, y3, z3);
313        }
314        // Add contributions from each corner to get the final noise value.
315        // The result is clamped to stay just inside [-1,1]
316        return Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, 31.5 * n));
317        //return (32.0 * n) * 1.25086885 + 0.0003194984;
318    }

320    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final double w, final long seed) {
321        double n = 0.0;
322        final double s = (x + y + z + w) * F4;
323        final int i = fastFloor(x + s), j = fastFloor(y + s), k = fastFloor(z + s), l = fastFloor(w + s);
324        final double[] gradient4DLUT = grad4d;
325        final double t = (i + j + k + l) * G4,
326                X0 = i - t,
327                Y0 = j - t,
328                Z0 = k - t,
329                W0 = l - t,
330                x0 = x - X0,
331                y0 = y - Y0,
332                z0 = z - Z0,
333                w0 = w - W0;
334        final int c = (x0 > y0 ? 128 : 0) | (x0 > z0 ? 64 : 0) | (y0 > z0 ? 32 : 0) | (x0 > w0 ? 16 : 0) | (y0 > w0 ? 8 : 0) | (z0 > w0 ? 4 : 0);
335        final int i1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] >>> 2,
336                j1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] >>> 2,
337                k1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] >>> 2,
338                l1 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] >>> 2,
339                i2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] >>> 1 & 1,
340                j2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] >>> 1 & 1,
341                k2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] >>> 1 & 1,
342                l2 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] >>> 1 & 1,
343                i3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c] & 1,
344                j3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 1] & 1,
345                k3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 2] & 1,
346                l3 = SIMPLEX_4D[c | 3] & 1;
347        final double x1 = x0 - i1 + G4,
348                y1 = y0 - j1 + G4,
349                z1 = z0 - k1 + G4,
350                w1 = w0 - l1 + G4,
351                x2 = x0 - i2 + 2 * G4,
352                y2 = y0 - j2 + 2 * G4,
353                z2 = z0 - k2 + 2 * G4,
354                w2 = w0 - l2 + 2 * G4,
355                x3 = x0 - i3 + 3 * G4,
356                y3 = y0 - j3 + 3 * G4,
357                z3 = z0 - k3 + 3 * G4,
358                w3 = w0 - l3 + 3 * G4,
359                x4 = x0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
360                y4 = y0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
361                z4 = z0 - 1 + 4 * G4,
362                w4 = w0 - 1 + 4 * G4;
363        final int h0 = (hash256(i, j, k, l, seed) & 0xFC),
364                h1 = (hash256(i + i1, j + j1, k + k1, l + l1, seed) & 0xFC),
365                h2 = (hash256(i + i2, j + j2, k + k2, l + l2, seed) & 0xFC),
366                h3 = (hash256(i + i3, j + j3, k + k3, l + l3, seed) & 0xFC),
367                h4 = (hash256(i + 1, j + 1, k + 1, l + 1, seed) & 0xFC);
368        double t0 = LIMIT4 - x0 * x0 - y0 * y0 - z0 * z0 - w0 * w0;
369        if(t0 > 0) {
370            t0 *= t0;
371            n += t0 * t0 * (x0 * gradient4DLUT[h0] + y0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 1] + z0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 2] + w0 * gradient4DLUT[h0 | 3]);
372        }
373        double t1 = LIMIT4 - x1 * x1 - y1 * y1 - z1 * z1 - w1 * w1;
374        if (t1 > 0) {
375            t1 *= t1;
376            n += t1 * t1 * (x1 * gradient4DLUT[h1] + y1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 1] + z1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 2] + w1 * gradient4DLUT[h1 | 3]);
377        }
378        double t2 = LIMIT4 - x2 * x2 - y2 * y2 - z2 * z2 - w2 * w2;
379        if (t2 > 0) {
380            t2 *= t2;
381            n += t2 * t2 * (x2 * gradient4DLUT[h2] + y2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 1] + z2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 2] + w2 * gradient4DLUT[h2 | 3]);
382        }
383        double t3 = LIMIT4 - x3 * x3 - y3 * y3 - z3 * z3 - w3 * w3;
384        if (t3 > 0) {
385            t3 *= t3;
386            n += t3 * t3 * (x3 * gradient4DLUT[h3] + y3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 1] + z3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 2] + w3 * gradient4DLUT[h3 | 3]);
387        }
388        double t4 = LIMIT4 - x4 * x4 - y4 * y4 - z4 * z4 - w4 * w4;
389        if (t4 > 0) {
390            t4 *= t4;
391            n += t4 * t4 * (x4 * gradient4DLUT[h4] + y4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 1] + z4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 2] + w4 * gradient4DLUT[h4 | 3]);
392        }
393        //return NumberTools.bounce(5.0 + 41.0 * n);
394        return Math.max(-1.0, Math.min(1.0, 14.75 * n));
395    }

397    /**
398     * Thanks to Mark A. Ropper for
399     * <a href="https://computergraphics.stackexchange.com/questions/6408/what-might-be-causing-these-artifacts-in-5d-6d-simplex-noise">this implementation</a>.
400     * @param x x coordinate
401     * @param y y coordinate
402     * @param z z coordinate
403     * @param w w coordinate (4th dimension)
404     * @param u u coordinate (5th dimension)
405     * @param seed long value that should completely change the noise if it changes even slightly
406     * @return a continuous noise value between -1.0 and 1.0, both inclusive
407     */
408    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z, final double w, final double u, final long seed) {
409        double n0, n1, n2, n3, n4, n5;
410        double t = (x + y + z + w + u) * F5;
411        int i = fastFloor(x + t);
412        int j = fastFloor(y + t);
413        int k = fastFloor(z + t);
414        int l = fastFloor(w + t);
415        int h = fastFloor(u + t);
416        t = (i + j + k + l + h) * G5;
417        double X0 = i - t;
418        double Y0 = j - t;
419        double Z0 = k - t;
420        double W0 = l - t;
421        double U0 = h - t;
422        double x0 = x - X0;
423        double y0 = y - Y0;
424        double z0 = z - Z0;
425        double w0 = w - W0;
426        double u0 = u - U0;
427
428        int rankx = 0;
429        int ranky = 0;
430        int rankz = 0;
431        int rankw = 0;
432        int ranku = 0;
433
434        if (x0 > y0) rankx++; else ranky++;
435        if (x0 > z0) rankx++; else rankz++;
436        if (x0 > w0) rankx++; else rankw++;
437        if (x0 > u0) rankx++; else ranku++;
438
439        if (y0 > z0) ranky++; else rankz++;
440        if (y0 > w0) ranky++; else rankw++;
441        if (y0 > u0) ranky++; else ranku++;
442
443        if (z0 > w0) rankz++; else rankw++;
444        if (z0 > u0) rankz++; else ranku++;
445
446        if (w0 > u0) rankw++; else ranku++;
447
448        int i1 = 3 - rankx >>> 31;
449        int j1 = 3 - ranky >>> 31;
450        int k1 = 3 - rankz >>> 31;
451        int l1 = 3 - rankw >>> 31;
452        int h1 = 3 - ranku >>> 31;
453
454        int i2 = 2 - rankx >>> 31;
455        int j2 = 2 - ranky >>> 31;
456        int k2 = 2 - rankz >>> 31;
457        int l2 = 2 - rankw >>> 31;
458        int h2 = 2 - ranku >>> 31;
459
460        int i3 = 1 - rankx >>> 31;
461        int j3 = 1 - ranky >>> 31;
462        int k3 = 1 - rankz >>> 31;
463        int l3 = 1 - rankw >>> 31;
464        int h3 = 1 - ranku >>> 31;
465
466        int i4 = -rankx >>> 31;
467        int j4 = -ranky >>> 31;
468        int k4 = -rankz >>> 31;
469        int l4 = -rankw >>> 31;
470        int h4 = -ranku >>> 31;
471
472        double x1 = x0 - i1 + G5;
473        double y1 = y0 - j1 + G5;
474        double z1 = z0 - k1 + G5;
475        double w1 = w0 - l1 + G5;
476        double u1 = u0 - h1 + G5;
477
478        double x2 = x0 - i2 + 2 * G5;
479        double y2 = y0 - j2 + 2 * G5;
480        double z2 = z0 - k2 + 2 * G5;
481        double w2 = w0 - l2 + 2 * G5;
482        double u2 = u0 - h2 + 2 * G5;
483
484        double x3 = x0 - i3 + 3 * G5;
485        double y3 = y0 - j3 + 3 * G5;
486        double z3 = z0 - k3 + 3 * G5;
487        double w3 = w0 - l3 + 3 * G5;
488        double u3 = u0 - h3 + 3 * G5;
489
490        double x4 = x0 - i4 + 4 * G5;
491        double y4 = y0 - j4 + 4 * G5;
492        double z4 = z0 - k4 + 4 * G5;

566    public static double noise(final double x, final double y, final double z,
567                               final double w, final double u, final double v, final long seed) {
568        final double s = (x + y + z + w + u + v) * F6;
569
570        final int skewX = fastFloor(x + s), skewY = fastFloor(y + s), skewZ = fastFloor(z + s),
571                skewW = fastFloor(w + s), skewU = fastFloor(u + s), skewV = fastFloor(v + s);
572        final double[] m = mShared, cellDist = cellDistShared, gradient6DLUT = SeededNoise.grad6d;
573        final int[] distOrder = distOrderShared,
574                intLoc = intLocShared;
575        intLoc[0] = skewX;
576        intLoc[1] = skewY;
577        intLoc[2] = skewZ;
578        intLoc[3] = skewW;
579        intLoc[4] = skewU;
580        intLoc[5] = skewV;
581
582        final double unskew = (skewX + skewY + skewZ + skewW + skewU + skewV) * G6;
583        cellDist[0] = x - skewX + unskew;
584        cellDist[1] = y - skewY + unskew;
585        cellDist[2] = z - skewZ + unskew;
586        cellDist[3] = w - skewW + unskew;
587        cellDist[4] = u - skewU + unskew;
588        cellDist[5] = v - skewV + unskew;
589
590        int o0 = (cellDist[0]<cellDist[1]?1:0)+(cellDist[0]<cellDist[2]?1:0)+(cellDist[0]<cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[0]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[0]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
591        int o1 = (cellDist[1]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[2]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[1]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
592        int o2 = (cellDist[2]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<=cellDist[1]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[3]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[2]<cellDist[5]?1:0);
593        int o3 = (cellDist[3]<=cellDist[0]?1:0)+(cellDist[3]<=cellDist[1]?1:0)+(cellDist[3]<=cellDist[2]?1:0)+(cellDist[3]<cellDist[4]?1:0)+(cellDist[3]<cellDist[5]?1:0);

598        distOrder[o1]=1;
599        distOrder[o2]=2;
600        distOrder[o3]=3;
601        distOrder[o4]=4;
602        distOrder[o5]=5;
603
604        double n = 0;
605        double skewOffset = 0;
606
607        for (int c = -1; c < 6; c++) {
608            if (c != -1) intLoc[distOrder[c]]++;
609
610            m[0] = cellDist[0] - (intLoc[0] - skewX) + skewOffset;
611            m[1] = cellDist[1] - (intLoc[1] - skewY) + skewOffset;
612            m[2] = cellDist[2] - (intLoc[2] - skewZ) + skewOffset;
613            m[3] = cellDist[3] - (intLoc[3] - skewW) + skewOffset;
614            m[4] = cellDist[4] - (intLoc[4] - skewU) + skewOffset;
615            m[5] = cellDist[5] - (intLoc[5] - skewV) + skewOffset;
616
617            double tc = LIMIT6;
618
619            for (int d = 0; d < 6; d++) {
620                tc -= m[d] * m[d];
621            }
622
623            if (tc > 0) {
624                final int h = hash256(intLoc[0], intLoc[1], intLoc[2], intLoc[3],
625                        intLoc[4], intLoc[5], seed) * 6;
626                final double gr = gradient6DLUT[h] * m[0] + gradient6DLUT[h + 1] * m[1]
627                        + gradient6DLUT[h + 2] * m[2] + gradient6DLUT[h + 3] * m[3]
628                        + gradient6DLUT[h + 4] * m[4] + gradient6DLUT[h + 5] * m[5];
629                tc *= tc;
630                n += gr * tc * tc;
631            }
632            skewOffset += G6;
633        }
634        return 7.5f * n;
635    }
